%N A371396 Maximum number of vertices of a chordal ring graph with diameter n.
%C A371396 Given integers N (even) and c (odd) the chordal ring graph CR(N,c) is a bipartite graph with vertex set Z_N, and edges {i,i+1}, {i,i-1}, {i,i+c} if i is odd, and {i,i-c} if i is even.
%C A371396 If the conjecture below holds, then a(n) = 2*A309805(n) for n >= 3.
%D A371396 P. Morillo, F. Comellas, and M. A. Fiol, The optimization of chordal ring networks, Communication Technology, Eds. Q. Yasheng and W Xiuying, World Scientific,1987, pages 295--299.
