%H A371396 M. A. Reyes, C. Dalf√≥, and M. A. Fiol, <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2409.00520">Structural and Spectral Properties of Chordal Ring, Multi-ring and Mixed Graphs</a>, arXiv:2409.00520 [math.CO2024], 2024 [See Table 6, p. 21]. Also in <a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/sym16091135">Symmetry</a> 16 (2024), no. 9, 1135.
%H A371396 J. L. A. Yebra, M. A. Fiol, P. Morillo, and I. Alegre, <a href="https://upcommons.upc.edu/handle/2117/12662">The diameter of undirected graphs associated to plane tessellations</a>, Ars Combin. 20-B (1985), 159-171.
%F A371396 a(n) = (3*n^2+1)/2 if n is odd.
%F A371396 Conjecture: a(n) = (3/2)*n^2 - n if n is even and n > 2.
%e A371396 For diameter n=3 the maximum number of vertices a(3)=14 is attained by the Heawood graph.
